snapper
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:any of a group of edible pinkish-white fish found in Australian and New Zealand waters; also spelt incorrectly schnapper; also called tamure
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
